FBIS4-43389 "drweu116_j_94002" FBIS-WEU-94-116 Daily Report 16 Jun 1994 ITALY & VATICAN CITY Northern League Pledges Full Support for Government Northern League Pledges Full Support for Government LD1606082594 Rome RAI Televideo Teletext in Italian 0452 GMT 16 Jun 94 LD1606082594 Rome RAI Televideo Teletext Italian BFN [Text] The first meeting of the Northern League's federal political secretariat ended shortly after midnight. During the meeting, matters pertaining to the organization and work of League leaders in national institutions were discussed. The League confirmed its full support for the government. Institutional Reforms Minister Francesco Speroni also explained the meaning of the words laborism and independence. Laborism is understood as "nonconservatism" and independence as "a faction of constructive criticism" within the government, which "propels the League into goverment."
